heaviest_rainfall.status: On 04 January 2025, a record rainfall of 36.8mm was measured, indicating an exceptionally wet day.  4.6mm per hour was recorded as falling at times during the 37.2 hour storm.

heaviest_rainrate.status: Today, the rain fell at an intense rate peaking at 10.1mm per hour, one of the heaviest downpours recorded and ranked 10th from our records.  The precipitation lasted 16.5 hours and dumped 9.37mm in total.  The heaviest rain was recorded on 02 September 2025 with a peak rate of 27.0mm per hour.  The storm lasted 15.0 hours and had a total rainfall of 21.19mm.

longest_rain.status: Today's rainstorm ranked 10th on our record table for the length of the storm as it lasted 16.5 hours; it delivered 9.37mm of rain at a maximum rate of 10.1mm per hour.  The longest rain storm on record lasted 37.2 hours on 04 January 2025 when 36.8mm of rain fell and at one point was falling at 4.6mm per hour.
